This paper proposes a machine learning algorithm for learning a Mahalanobis metric from data. This is a common problem in several subfields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which are relevant to the subfield of signal processing (cs.SD). Finally, the paper involves linear algebra techniques, which are relevant to the subfield of information theory (cs.IT).
